ly breaks down clear boundaries between Chinese and non-Chinese thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGlobalization. 0aHumanities. 0aPhilosophy, Chinese. 0aSocial sciences. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aSociology : Social Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh1 aJenco, Leigh, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846046840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438460468423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438460468/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles